    "We then engage in an analysis of societal and ethical implications of the discourse, and end with conclusions and discussion.",
    "Existential threat argument, effective altruism and longtermism in AI hypeTalking about existential threats posed by advanced technologies is not a recent phenomenon.",
    "Science fiction writers have for long created scenarios of machines more powerful than humans taking over the world, painting both utopian and dystopian pictures of such futures.",
    "In the current discussions, however, the proposed existential threats of AI are not being discussed as science fiction but as actual concerns that allegedly could be realised in the near future.",
    "In this paper, the term Existential Threat Argument (ETA) refers to statements according to which developing an AGI that surpasses human intelligence is possible, if not inevitable, and which can-if not controlled-lead to human extinction."
